ingredients: "2 loin pork chops<>3 tablespoons soy sauce<>3 tablespoons dry vermouth (or sherry)<>1 clove garlic (minced)<>3 scallions (chopped)<>ground pepper<>1 tablespoon peanut or vegetable oil<>1/2 cup dry white wine<>coarse salt (to taste)",
steps: "Marinate chops in mixture of soy sauce, garlic, scallions and pepper at least 2 hours (or overnight)||Heat oil in skillet. Remove chops from marinade and brown on both sides. Add marinade and wine. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Turning once or until pork is whitish-pink in center and tender. Be careful not to overcook. Season with salt and pepper.||Remove chops. Reduce juices in pan and pour over chops."
